HEADWORD: Crownwork
<hw>Crown"work`</hw> <pr>(-w?rk`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Fort.)</fld>
<def>A work consisting of two or more bastioned fronts, with their
outworks, covering an enceinte, a bridgehead, etc., and connected by
wings with the main work or the river bank.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crow-quill</ent>⟦br⟧
